        "type": "message",
        "text": "When I started programming, my code was running on a pc with only ram and no hard drives, it loaded os from 5.25'\u2019 floppy disks (attached). The current code of mine runs in CloudFlare servers which, I think, are also all in ram mostly. The only difference is that my code was running locally, and now it\u2019s distributed worldwide. Well, this was an attempt to hilariously say that there was little revolution. Whilst in reality, heck, it changed gazzilion times!\n\nBack then 25 ago I was coding with PolyPascal on monochromic monitor, writting loops and if conditions. Now my screen shows VSCode in almost nearly-monochromic color scheme, am still writting ifs and loops mostly:). Really - not much has changed.\n\nSo - agree 100%.",
